{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9b2c95f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3611"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3611"},"text":"§ 3611.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Payment of a fine or restitution","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A person who is sentenced to pay a fine, assessment, or restitution, shall pay the fine, assessment, or restitution (including any interest or penalty), as specified by the Director of the Administrative Office of the United States Courts. Such Director may specify that such payment be made to the clerk of the court or in the manner provided for under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s604/a/18"},"text":"section 604(a)(18) of title 28","children":[],"tail":", United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9b2c960-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/tII/s212/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473, title II, § 212(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2004"},"text":"98 Stat. 2004","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/185/s10/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–185, § 10(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1283"},"text":"101 Stat. 1283","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tXXXV/s3591"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title XXXV, § 3591","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4931"},"text":"104 Stat. 4931","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/132/tII/s207/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–132, title II, § 207(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-24"},"text":"Apr. 24, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1237"},"text":"110 Stat. 1237","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9b2c961-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb9b2c962-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb9b2c963-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For a prior section 3611, applicable to offenses committed prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1987","children":[],"tail":", see note set out preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3601"},"text":"section 3601 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb9b2c964-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/132"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–132","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Payment of a fine or restitution” for “Payment of a fine” in section catchline and “, assessment, or restitution, shall pay the fine, assessment, or restitution” for “or assessment shall pay the fine or assessment” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":" substituted “604(a)(18)” for “604(a)(17)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/185"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–185","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section read as follows: “A person who has been sentenced to pay a fine pursuant to the provisions of subchapter C of chapter 227 shall pay the fine immediately, or by the time and method specified by the sentencing court, to the clerk of the court. The clerk shall forward the payment to the United States Treasury.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb9b2c965-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb9b2c966-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/132"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–132","children":[],"tail":" to be effective, to extent constitutionally permissible, for sentencing proceedings in cases in which defendant is convicted on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-24"},"text":"Apr. 24, 1996","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/132/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Pub. L. 104–132","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2248"},"text":"section 2248 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb9b2c967-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1987 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/185/s10/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–185, § 10(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1283"},"text":"101 Stat. 1283","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/185/s10/b"},"text":"“The amendment made by this section [amending this section] shall apply with respect to any fine imposed after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1988","children":[],"tail":". Such amendment shall also apply with respect to any fine imposed on or before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1988","children":[],"tail":", if the fine remains uncollected as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-02-01"},"text":"February 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":", unless the Director of the Administrative Office of the United States Courts determines further delay is necessary. If the Director so determines, the amendment made by this section shall apply with respect to any such fine imposed on or before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1988","children":[],"tail":", if the fine remains uncollected as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-05-01"},"text":"May 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb9b2c968-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1987","children":[],"tail":", and applicable only to offenses committed after the taking effect of this section, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/s235/a/1"},"text":"section 235(a)(1) of Pub. L. 98–473","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3551"},"text":"section 3551 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb9b2c969-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Receipt of Fines—Interim Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/185/s9"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–185, § 9","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1282"},"text":"101 Stat. 1282","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/185/s9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"November","children":[],"tail":" 1, 1987, "},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"to April","children":[],"tail":" 30, 1988.—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3611"},"text":"section 3611 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, a person who, during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-11-01"},"text":"November 1, 1987","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-04-30"},"text":"April 30, 1988","children":[],"tail":", is sentenced to pay a fine or assessment shall pay the fine or assessment (including any interest or penalty) to the clerk of the court, with respect to an offense committed on or before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1984","children":[],"tail":", and to the Attorney General, with respect to an offense committed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1984","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"May","children":[],"tail":" 1, 1988, "},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"to October","children":[],"tail":" 31, 1988.—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3611"},"text":"section 3611 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, a person who during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-05-01"},"text":"May 1, 1988","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-31"},"text":"October 31, 1988","children":[],"tail":", is sentenced to pay a fine or assessment shall pay the fine or assessment in accordance with this subsection."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In a case initiated by citation or violation notice, such person shall pay the fine or assessment (including any interest or penalty), as specified by the Director of the Administrative Office of the United States Courts. Such Director may specify that such payment be made to the clerk of the court or in the manner provided for under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s604/a/17"},"text":"section 604(a)(17) of title 28","children":[],"tail":", United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In any other case, such person shall pay the fine or assessment (including any interest or penalty) to the clerk of the court, with respect to an offense committed on or before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1984","children":[],"tail":", and to the Attorney General, with respect to an offense committed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1984","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
